text.tspan: 4.15.4STAFF PLACEMENT PROCEDUREAfter the candidate has been approved and meets the medical fitness requirements of the vessel’s Flag and charterer, necessarytravel arrangements, immigration formalities and pre-departure briefing shall be completed.During the pre-departure briefing the technical details and trade of the vessel as well as the past performance of the staff shall bediscussed. The staff shall also be briefed about the Company’s policies and the expectations of the company.The seafarer's personal records in the Phoenix Crew Management Module shall be suitably updated. In the case of new applicants anew identification number shall be given.A standard “Contract of Employment” specifying the terms and conditions of service shall be signed by all Officers and ratings at thetime of the Seafarers assignment on board. For reasons such as unavailability of suitable replacement, owing to time constraints,possibilities of effecting emergency transfer from another vessel shall be considered, in which case it shall be treated as acontinuation of service.The check of documentation and certification, which includes expiry dates of certificates among other checks are carried out asapplicable at each stage of the joining processes such as proposal, travel, sign on, etc.4.15.5RE-EMPLOYMENT OF STAFF WHO HAVE BEEN DISMISSEDStaff who have been dismissed on disciplinary grounds or due to an incident shall only be re-employed after appropriate andsatisfactory training/ rehabilitation has been carried to address the root cause/ inadequacy which led to the incident, so as to preventrecurrence.4.15.6REVIEW OF SHIP STAFF RECRUITMENT PROCESSTo ensure its continued effectiveness the ship’s staff selection and recruitment process, review of the selection and recruitmentprocess shall be carried out once every year and documented in the Annual Management Review.HSEQA Superintendent shall be responsible for documenting such records and submitting to the appropriate responsible person for necessary follow-up action.4.15.7SECURITY CHECKS FOR EMPLOYEESCompany has set up the following procedure to ensure that appropriate security checks are undertaken for employees.1. All employees have to self declare their security status in form OC9 Pre-joining Biodata.2. In case any response to the security queries, in the form, is affirmative, then company will only recruit the individual after a Police verification or equivalent securitycheck has been carried out, to confirm that the individual is a law abiding person.3. Company will carry out random security checks of at least 5% of it's employees by means of Police verification or equivalent.4.16CERTIFICATION PROCEDUREThe company has within its management vessels of various flags having their own certification requirement and applicationprocedures. In addition vessels are also required to be in compliance with additional Industry Training requirements as stipulated bythe Charterers.At the time of appointment of any staff, the Manning office/ Manning agent responsible shall verify whether the Officer and crew is inpossession of the requisite National licenses, STCW endorsements/ certificates and the applicable certificates/ documents required bythe flag state and Charterers of the vessel being appointed.Authentication of certificate of competency/ watch keeping certificate in case of certified officers/ ratings and authentication of CDC’sor other equivalent document in case of uncertified officer/ rating will be carried out for all staff.Authentication of Industry certificates is also to be carried out for all staff by verifying with the issuing authority or other recognisedbody such as "OPITO" to confirm that a) The Institute is approved to conduct the relevant course and b) The Certificate is genuine andhas been issued by the Institute.The Company has registered with OPITO Vantage Central Register which allows on line verification of documents.Primary check is to be carried by the Manning Office/ Manning Agent and Secondary Check is to be carried out by Head Office.The above process is to be documented in the Phoenix 'Crew' module".Application for Flag state endorsement shall be processed through the local/ foreign consulates/ Authorities/ Agencies and it will beensured that all crew members onboard shall comply with the flag state requirement of the vessel.As applicable, the filing agents or the licensing authorities shall issue certificate of Receipt of Application (CRA) to the applicant, whichnormally has a validity of three months.Before expiry of the CRA the full term licenses/ documents or qualification document, as applicable, are followed up and forwarded tothe vessel.Crew Certificate and document details including expiry are available on board and ashore in the PHOENIX system and the Office isresponsible to ensure that the validity of the documents is maintained. Master shall also keep track as a back up and inform the officeimmediately in case of any shortfalls / deficiencies or documents due to expire.4.16.1NATIONAL LICENSESThe seamen are individually responsible for ensuring validity of their national licenses. The manning offices will assist if necessary inthis process.4.16.2RESPONSIBILITYManning Office/ Manning Agents shall be responsible to ensure that all vessel personnel are certified in accordance to the flagrequirement and also for processing necessary applications. The Manning Office/ Manning Agent shall oversee itsproper executionand also keep track of all expenses related to certification in order to make recovery where applicable from the concerned staff, forwhich the vessel shall be duly advised.
